<p>If you provide no arguments, Lens will run all of your tests:</p>

<div class="terminal">
	<div>Run all of your tests:</div>
	<pre><code>lens</code></pre>
</div>

<p>But if you provide an optional path argument, Lens will run only those tests that you specify:</p>

<div class="terminal">
	<div>Run some of your tests:</div>
	<pre><code>lens <i>./tests/MyFile.php</i> <i>./tests/MyDirectory/</i></code></pre>
</div>


<h2>Reports</h2>

<p>Lens can provide reports in different formats.
This is mainly useful for continuous integration.</p>

<div class="terminal">
	<div>Generate a <a href="https://testanything.org/">TAP</a> report:</div>
	<pre><code>lens --report=tap</code></pre>
</div>
